# Public distribution repo — it must NEVER contain credentials, source code,
# or CI workflows. Deny everything by default and explicitly allow only the
# files this repo is meant to track; release bundles are attached as
# Release assets, never committed.
#
# This file is the source of truth for the public repo's .gitignore — the
# publish-landing workflow syncs it along with README.md and docs/.
#
# The docs/ folder is the GitHub Pages landing site (static SPA + showcase).
*
!README.md
!.gitignore
!docs/
docs/*
!docs/index.html
!docs/privacy.html
!docs/favicon.svg
!docs/.nojekyll
!docs/js/
!docs/js/*.js
!docs/i18n/
!docs/i18n/*.json

# Showcase / demo assets shown on the site. Only screenshot (.png) and
# walkthrough video (.webm) files are allowed — never source or credentials.
# Captured from the fully fictional demo study, so they contain no real PHI.
!docs/showcase/
!docs/showcase/screenshots/
!docs/showcase/screenshots/*.png
!docs/showcase/video/
!docs/showcase/video/*.webm
